publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'college-of-southern-nevada', '', '', '2013-08-01 07:30:19', '2013-08-01 07:30:19', '', '0', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/?post_type=participant&#038;p=495', '0', 'participant', '', '0'), ('496', '5', '2013-07-31 06:53:43', '2013-07-31 06:53:43', '[people]\r\n\r\n<h1>Project Participants</h1>\r\n\r\n<figure><a title=\"The Nevada System of Higher Education.\" href=\"http://www.nevada.edu\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"height: 50px; width: 50px;\" title=\"The Nevada System of Higher Education.\" alt=\"NSHE\" src=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/images/Institution%20logos/NSHE.svg\" /></a>\r\n<figcaption><a title=\"The Nevada System of Higher Education.\" href=\"http://www.nevada.edu\" target=\"_blank\">Nevada System of Higher Education</a></figcaption></figure><figure><a title=\"Great Basin College.\" href=\"http://www.gbcnv.edu/\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"height: 50px; width: 50px;\" title=\"Great Basin College.\" alt=\"GBC\" src=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/images/Institution%20logos/GBC.svg\" /></a>\r\n<figcaption><a title=\"Great Basin College.\" href=\"http://www.gbcnv.edu/\" target=\"_blank\">Great Basin College</a></figcaption></figure><figure><a title=\"The Desert Research Institute.\" href=\"http://www.dri.edu\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"height: 50px; width: 50px;\" title=\"The Desert Research Institute.\" alt=\"DRI\" src=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/images/Institution%20logos/DRI.svg\" /></a>\r\n<figcaption><a title=\"The Desert Research Institute.\" href=\"http://www.dri.edu\" target=\"_blank\">Desert Research Institute</a></figcaption></figure><figure><a title=\"Nevada State College.\" href=\"http://nsc.nevada.edu\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"height: 50px; width: 50px;\" title=\"Nevada State College.\" alt=\"NSC\" src=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/images/Institution%20logos/NSC.svg\" /></a>\r\n<figcaption><a title=\"Nevada State College.\" href=\"http://nsc.nevada.edu\" target=\"_blank\">Nevada State College</a></figcaption></figure><figure><a title=\"The University of Nevada, Las Vegas.\" href=\"http://www.unlv.edu\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"height: 50px; width: 50px;\" title=\"The University of Nevada, Las Vegas.\" alt=\"UNLV\" src=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/images/Institution%20logos/UNLV.svg\" /></a>\r\n<figcaption><a title=\"The University of Nevada, Las Vegas.\" href=\"http://www.unlv.edu\" target=\"_blank\">University of Nevada, Las Vegas</a></figcaption></figure><figure><a title=\"Truckee Meadows Community College.\" href=\"http://www.tmcc.edu/\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"height: 50px; width: 50px;\" title=\"Truckee Meadows Community College.\" alt=\"TMCC\" src=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/images/Institution%20logos/TMCC.svg\" /></a>\r\n<figcaption><a title=\"Truckee Meadows Community College.\" href=\"http://www.tmcc.edu/\" target=\"_blank\">Truckee Meadows Community College</a></figcaption></figure><figure><a title=\"The University of Nevada, Reno.\" href=\"http://www.unr.edu\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"height: 50px; width: 50px;\" title=\"The University of Nevada, Reno.\" alt=\"NSHE\" src=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/images/Institution%20logos/UNR.svg\" /></a>\r\n<figcaption><a title=\"The University of Nevada, Reno.\" href=\"http://www.unr.edu\" target=\"_blank\">University of Nevada, Reno</a></figcaption></figure><figure><a title=\"Western Nevada College.\" href=\"http://www.wnc.edu/\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"height: 50px; width: 50px;\" title=\"Western Nevada College.\" alt=\"WNC\" src=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/images/Institution%20logos/WNC.svg\" /></a>\r\n<figcaption><a title=\"Western Nevada College.\" href=\"http://www.wnc.edu/\" target=\"_blank\">Western Nevada College</a></figcaption></figure><figure><a title=\"College of Southern Nevada.\" href=\"http://www.csn.edu/\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"height: 50px; width: 50px;\" title=\"College of Southern Nevada.\" alt=\"CSN\" src=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/images/Institution%20logos/CSN.svg\" /></a>\r\n<figcaption><a title=\"College of Southern Nevada.\" href=\"http://www.csn.edu/\" target=\"_blank\">College of Southern Nevada</a></figcaption></figure>', 'People', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '17-revision-9', '', '', '2013-07-31 06:53:43', '2013-07-31 06:53:43', '', '17', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/17-revision-9/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('558', '5', '2013-09-08 04:56:23', '2013-09-08 04:56:23', '', 'Get Data', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'get-data', '', '', '2013-09-08 04:59:05', '2013-09-08 04:59:05', '', '0', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/?p=558', '2', 'nav_menu_item', '', '0'), ('378', '5', '2013-07-29 00:24:01', '2013-07-29 00:24:01', 'This series of activities is adapted from a climate change activity manual that was created to aid science teachers in bringing climate change science to their classrooms in an approachable and relevant way. The activities and lessons contained in the manual represent the best work of some of the Washoe County School District elementary, middle and high school teachers who participated in the EPSCoR climate change educational institutes held over four summers at the University of Nevada, Reno from 2009 to 2012.\r\n\r\nActivities and lessons were written for teacher use in the Reno, Nevada area but the authors and manual editors believe that a wider application can be reached in other parts of the country and of the world. Lessons can be modified to fit specialized schools and programs that include units on climate change or environmental science. High school and middle school lessons can be modified to fit elementary programs. We believe that science teachers are very good at modifying lessons for their own unique circumstances! Each of the lessons and activities have been implemented in public school science classes and were designed specifically for practical use. Please let the authors know of your successes with their plans and feel free to submit your own original lessons to the EPSCoR Nevada-UNR Director(s) for inclusion in an upcoming second edition of the Climate Change Activity Manual.\r\n\r\nThe activity manual was organized by grade level and can be accessed on the Nevada Climate Change Portal as follows:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>#1 – Introduction: has information about the project and contact information for manual editor, <a href=\"mailto:jacque@unr.edu\">Jacque Ewing-Taylor, Ph.D.</a>, along with descriptions and information on both the 5E model of science lesson construction and inquiry-based science education theory and implementation.</li>\r\n	<li>#2-5 – Elementary School Activities</li>\r\n	<li>#6-14 – Middle School Activities</li>\r\n	<li>#15-25 – High School Activities</li>\r\n	<li>#26 – Appendix from the Manual: Article on The Socratic Method, to be used in conjunction with activity #11 Alternative Fuels Activity</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Science Activities', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'science-activities', '', '', '2013-07-29 00:24:22', '2013-07-29 00:24:22', '', '13', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/?page_id=378', '0', 'page', '', '0'), ('379', '5', '2013-07-29 00:23:24', '2013-07-29 00:23:24', '', 'Science Activities', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '378-revision', '', '', '2013-07-29 00:23:24', '2013-07-29 00:23:24', '', '378', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/378-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('380', '5', '2013-07-29 00:24:01', '2013-07-29 00:24:01', 'This series of activities is adapted from a climate change activity manual that was created to aid science teachers in bringing climate change science to their classrooms in an approachable and relevant way. The activities and lessons contained in the manual represent the best work of some of the Washoe County School District elementary, middle and high school teachers who participated in the EPSCoR climate change educational institutes held over four summers at the University of Nevada, Reno from 2009 to 2012.\r\n\r\nActivities and lessons were written for teacher use in the Reno, Nevada area but the authors and manual editors believe that a wider application can be reached in other parts of the country and of the world. Lessons can be modified to fit specialized schools and programs that include units on climate change or environmental science. High school and middle school lessons can be modified to fit elementary programs. We believe that science teachers are very good at modifying lessons for their own unique circumstances! Each of the lessons and activities have been implemented in public school science classes and were designed specifically for practical use. Please let the authors know of your successes with their plans and feel free to submit your own original lessons to the EPSCoR Nevada-UNR Director(s) for inclusion in an upcoming second edition of the Climate Change Activity Manual.\r\n\r\nThe activity manual was organized by grade level and can be accessed on the Nevada Climate Change Portal as follows:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>#1 – Introduction: has information about the project and contact information for manual editor, <a href=\"mailto:jacque@unr.edu\">Jacque Ewing-Taylor, Ph.D.</a>, along with descriptions and information on both the 5E model of science lesson construction and inquiry-based science education theory and implementation.</li>\r\n	<li>#2-5 – Elementary School Activities</li>\r\n	<li>#6-14 – Middle School Activities</li>\r\n	<li>#15-25 – High School Activities</li>\r\n	<li>#26 – Appendix from the Manual: Article on The Socratic Method, to be used in conjunction with activity #11 Alternative Fuels Activity</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Science Activities', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '378-revision-2', '', '', '2013-07-29 00:24:01', '2013-07-29 00:24:01', '', '378', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/378-revision-2/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('381', '5', '2013-07-29 00:25:53', '2013-07-29 00:25:53', 'Publications created as a part of the Nevada Climate Change Project, or relating to the topic of climate change, are organized by the format or purpose of the document. The following categories contain all documents produced by, for, or related to the project and its interests.\r\n<h2>2013</h2>\r\n<h3>Journal Articles</h3>\r\nZang, C., and F. Biondi. Dendroclimatic calibration in R: The bootRes package for response and correlation function analysis. Dendrochronologia (in press), 2013, doi: 10.1016/j.dendro.2012.08.001\r\n\r\nDittrich, A., Gunes, M. H., and Dascalu, S. (2013). Network analysis of software repositories: Identifying subject matter experts. In Menezes, R., Evsukoff, A., and Gonzáles, M.C. (editors), Complex Networks, Studies in Computational Intelligence, vol. 424, 2013, pp. 187-198, Springer-Verlag, doi 10.1007/978-3-642-30287-9_20.\r\n<h3>Conference Presentations</h3>\r\nReed, S., Reed, T., and Dascalu, S.M. (2013). Coupling Recursive Hyperspheric Classification with Linear Discriminant Analysis for Improved Results. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Information Technology: New Generations (ITNG-2013), Las Vegas, NV, April 2013.\r\n\r\nVesco, J., Harris, F.C., Jr., Dascalu, S.M., Jackson, D., and Baker, J.E. (2013). Semi-Automated Analysis Software for a Novel Biochemistry Assay. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Information Technology: New Generations (ITNG-2013), Las Vegas, NV, April 2013.\r\n\r\nPatel, J., Okamoto, S., Dascalu, S.M., and Harris, F.C., Jr. (2013). A Web-enabled Approach for Generating Data Processors. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Information Technology: New Generations (ITNG-2013), Las Vegas, NV, April 2013.\r\n\r\nGibbs, I., Dascalu, S.M., and Harris, F.C., Jr. (2013). Web Portal Usability Tests for the Nevada Climate Change Portal. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Information Technology: New Generations (ITNG-2013), Las Vegas, NV, April 2013.\r\n\r\nRavi, L., Yan, Q., Dascalu, S., and Harris, F.C., Jr (2013). A Survey of Visualization Techniques and Tools for Environmental Data. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Computers and Their Applications (CATA-2013), Honolulu, HI, April 2013.\r\n\r\nYan, Q., McMahon, M., Jr., Dascalu, S., and Harris, F.C., Jr., Ravi, L. (2013). Community Metadata ISO 19115 Adaptor. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Computers and Their Applications (CATA-2013), Honolulu, HI, April 2013.\r\n\r\nSharifahmadian, E. and S. Latifi, “Water Environment Risk Prediction Using Bayesian Network,” IEEE Conference, Data Mining and Machine Learning, SoutheastCon 2013, Jacksonville, Florida, USA, April 4-7, 2013 (under review).\r\n\r\nPublications from other years: <a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Libraries/Publications/2013.aspx\">2013</a> • <a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Libraries/Publications/2012.aspx\">2012</a> • <a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Libraries/Publications/2011.aspx\">2011</a> • <a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Libraries/Publications/2010.aspx\">2010</a> • <a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Libraries/Publications/2009.aspx\">2009</a>', 'Publications', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'publications', '', '', '2013-08-13 03:46:34', '2013-08-13 03:46:34', '', '13', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/?page_id=381', '0', 'page', '', '0'), ('382', '5', '2013-07-29 00:25:18', '2013-07-29 00:25:18', '', 'Publications', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '381-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-07-29 00:25:18', '2013-07-29 00:25:18', '', '381', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/381-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('383', '5', '2013-07-29 00:25:53', '2013-07-29 00:25:53', 'Publications created as a part of the Nevada Climate Change Project, or relating to the topic of climate change, are organized by the format or purpose of the document. The following categories contain all documents produced by, for, or related to the project and its interests.\r\n<h3>2013</h3>\r\n<h4>Journal Articles</h4>\r\nZang, C., and F. Biondi. Dendroclimatic calibration in R: The bootRes package for response and correlation function analysis. Dendrochronologia (in press), 2013, doi: 10.1016/j.dendro.2012.08.001\r\n\r\nDittrich, A., Gunes, M. H., and Dascalu, S. (2013). Network analysis of software repositories: Identifying subject matter experts. In Menezes, R., Evsukoff, A., and Gonzáles, M.C. (editors), Complex Networks, Studies in Computational Intelligence, vol. 424, 2013, pp. 187-198, Springer-Verlag, doi 10.1007/978-3-642-30287-9_20.\r\n<h4>Conference Presentations</h4>\r\nReed, S., Reed, T., and Dascalu, S.M. (2013). Coupling Recursive Hyperspheric Classification with Linear Discriminant Analysis for Improved Results. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Information Technology: New Generations (ITNG-2013), Las Vegas, NV, April 2013.\r\n\r\nVesco, J., Harris, F.C., Jr., Dascalu, S.M., Jackson, D., and Baker, J.E. (2013). Semi-Automated Analysis Software for a Novel Biochemistry Assay. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Information Technology: New Generations (ITNG-2013), Las Vegas, NV, April 2013.\r\n\r\nPatel, J., Okamoto, S., Dascalu, S.M., and Harris, F.C., Jr. (2013). A Web-enabled Approach for Generating Data Processors. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Information Technology: New Generations (ITNG-2013), Las Vegas, NV, April 2013.\r\n\r\nGibbs, I., Dascalu, S.M., and Harris, F.C., Jr. (2013). Web Portal Usability Tests for the Nevada Climate Change Portal. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Information Technology: New Generations (ITNG-2013), Las Vegas, NV, April 2013.\r\n\r\nRavi, L., Yan, Q., Dascalu, S., and Harris, F.C., Jr (2013). A Survey of Visualization Techniques and Tools for Environmental Data. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Computers and Their Applications (CATA-2013), Honolulu, HI, April 2013.\r\n\r\nYan, Q., McMahon, M., Jr., Dascalu, S., and Harris, F.C., Jr., Ravi, L. (2013). Community Metadata ISO 19115 Adaptor. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Computers and Their Applications (CATA-2013), Honolulu, HI, April 2013.\r\n\r\nSharifahmadian, E. and S. Latifi, “Water Environment Risk Prediction Using Bayesian Network,” IEEE Conference, Data Mining and Machine Learning, SoutheastCon 2013, Jacksonville, Florida, USA, April 4-7, 2013 (under review).\r\n\r\nPublications from other years: <a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Libraries/Publications/2013.aspx\">2013</a> • <a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Libraries/Publications/2012.aspx\">2012</a> • <a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Libraries/Publications/2011.aspx\">2011</a> • <a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Libraries/Publications/2010.aspx\">2010</a> • <a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Libraries/Publications/2009.aspx\">2009</a>', 'Publications', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '381-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-07-29 00:25:53', '2013-07-29 00:25:53', '', '381', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/381-revision-2/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('468', '5', '2013-07-31 05:18:48', '2013-07-31 05:18:48', '', 'lynn-fenstermaker', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', 'lynn-fenstermaker-2', '', '', '2013-07-31 05:18:48', '2013-07-31 05:18:48', '', '0', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/lynn-fenstermaker.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('469', '5', '2013-07-31 05:18:50', '2013-07-31 05:18:50', '', 'mahesh-gautam', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', 'mahesh-gautam-2', '', '', '2013-07-31 05:18:50', '2013-07-31 05:18:50', '', '0', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/mahesh-gautam.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('470', '5', '2013-07-31 05:18:52', '2013-07-31 05:18:52', '', 'mark-walker', '',