alt=\"WNC\" src=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/images/Institution%20logos/WNC.svg\" /></a>\n<figcaption><a title=\"Western Nevada College.\" href=\"http://www.wnc.edu/\" target=\"_blank\">Western Nevada College</a></figcaption></figure><figure><a title=\"College of Southern Nevada.\" href=\"http://www.csn.edu/\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"height: 50px; width: 50px;\" title=\"College of Southern Nevada.\" alt=\"CSN\" src=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/images/Institution%20logos/CSN.svg\" /></a>\n<figcaption><a title=\"College of Southern Nevada.\" href=\"http://www.csn.edu/\" target=\"_blank\">College of Southern Nevada</a></figcaption></figure>', 'People', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '17-autosave', '', '', '2013-07-31 04:51:40', '2013-07-31 04:51:40', '', '17', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/17-autosave/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('400', '5', '2013-07-29 01:31:43', '2013-07-29 01:31:43', '', 'People Fields', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'people-fields', '', '', '2013-07-31 05:05:53', '2013-07-31 05:05:53', '', '0', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/wp-types-group/people-fields/', '0', 'wp-types-group', '', '0'), ('546', '5', '2013-08-04 22:56:27', '2013-08-04 22:56:27', 'Publications created as a part of the Nevada Climate Change Project, or relating to the topic of climate change, are organized by the format or purpose of the document. The following categories contain all documents produced by, for, or related to the project and its interests.\r\n<h2>2013</h2>\r\n<h4>Journal Articles</h4>\r\nZang, C., and F. Biondi. Dendroclimatic calibration in R: The bootRes package for response and correlation function analysis. Dendrochronologia (in press), 2013, doi: 10.1016/j.dendro.2012.08.001\r\n\r\nDittrich, A., Gunes, M. H., and Dascalu, S. (2013). Network analysis of software repositories: Identifying subject matter experts. In Menezes, R., Evsukoff, A., and Gonzáles, M.C. (editors), Complex Networks, Studies in Computational Intelligence, vol. 424, 2013, pp. 187-198, Springer-Verlag, doi 10.1007/978-3-642-30287-9_20.\r\n<h4>Conference Presentations</h4>\r\nReed, S., Reed, T., and Dascalu, S.M. (2013). Coupling Recursive Hyperspheric Classification with Linear Discriminant Analysis for Improved Results. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Information Technology: New Generations (ITNG-2013), Las Vegas, NV, April 2013.\r\n\r\nVesco, J., Harris, F.C., Jr., Dascalu, S.M., Jackson, D., and Baker, J.E. (2013). Semi-Automated Analysis Software for a Novel Biochemistry Assay. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Information Technology: New Generations (ITNG-2013), Las Vegas, NV, April 2013.\r\n\r\nPatel, J., Okamoto, S., Dascalu, S.M., and Harris, F.C., Jr. (2013). A Web-enabled Approach for Generating Data Processors. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Information Technology: New Generations (ITNG-2013), Las Vegas, NV, April 2013.\r\n\r\nGibbs, I., Dascalu, S.M., and Harris, F.C., Jr. (2013). Web Portal Usability Tests for the Nevada Climate Change Portal. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Information Technology: New Generations (ITNG-2013), Las Vegas, NV, April 2013.\r\n\r\nRavi, L., Yan, Q., Dascalu, S., and Harris, F.C., Jr (2013). A Survey of Visualization Techniques and Tools for Environmental Data. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Computers and Their Applications (CATA-2013), Honolulu, HI, April 2013.\r\n\r\nYan, Q., McMahon, M., Jr., Dascalu, S., and Harris, F.C., Jr., Ravi, L. (2013). Community Metadata ISO 19115 Adaptor. Accepted for publication in the Proceedings of the Intl. Conf. on Computers and Their Applications (CATA-2013), Honolulu, HI, April 2013.\r\n\r\nSharifahmadian, E. and S. Latifi, “Water Environment Risk Prediction Using Bayesian Network,” IEEE Conference, Data Mining and Machine Learning, SoutheastCon 2013, Jacksonville, Florida, USA, April 4-7, 2013 (under review).\r\n\r\nPublications from other years: <a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Libraries/Publications/2013.aspx\">2013</a> • <a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Libraries/Publications/2012.aspx\">2012</a> • <a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Libraries/Publications/2011.aspx\">2011</a> • <a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Libraries/Publications/2010.aspx\">2010</a> • <a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Libraries/Publications/2009.aspx\">2009</a>', 'Publications', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '381-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-08-04 22:56:27', '2013-08-04 22:56:27', '', '381', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/381-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('403', '5', '2013-07-29 01:48:19', '2013-07-29 01:48:19', '', 'Thomas Albright', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'thomas-albright', '', '', '2013-07-31 05:39:21', '2013-07-31 05:39:21', '', '0', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/?post_type=person&#038;p=403', '0', 'person', '', '0'), ('404', '5', '2013-07-29 01:49:11', '2013-07-29 01:49:11', '', 'Jay Arnone', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'jay-arnone', '', '', '2013-07-31 05:39:08', '2013-07-31 05:39:08', '', '0', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/?post_type=person&#038;p=404', '0', 'person', '', '0'), ('405', '5', '2013-07-29 01:49:53', '2013-07-29 01:49:53', '', 'Scott Bassett', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'scott-bassett', '', '', '2013-07-31 05:38:49', '2013-07-31 05:38:49', '', '0', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/?post_type=person&#038;p=405', '0', 'person', '', '0'), ('406', '5', '2013-07-29 01:50:31', '2013-07-29 01:50:31', '', 'Franco Biondi', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'franco-biondi', '', '', '2013-07-31 05:38:12', '2013-07-31 05:38:12', '', '0', 'http://m.nevadaclimatechange.com/?post_type=person&#038;p=406', '0', 'person', '', '0'), ('288', '5', '2012-12-11 17:24:17', '2012-12-11 17:24:17', '<h3> The Nevada Climate-ecohydrological Assessment Network (NevCAN)</h3>\r\n<section id=\"Main\">The Universities of Nevada (Las Vegas and Reno) and the Desert Research Institute have collaborated with land owner agencies in Nevada to establish two elevational transects of monitoring stations named the Nevada Climate-ecohydrology Assessment Network (NevCAN). The primary purpose of NevCAN is to collect data for long-term assessment of climate variability and change in Nevada and its impact on ecological and hydrological processes and function.These basin-to-mountain top transects are located in the Sheep Range (located approximately 35 km NNW of Las Vegas) and in the Snake Range (east central NV along the UT border; approximately 335 km NNE of Las Vegas). The Sheep Range transect has five monitoring stations beginning at 900 m and ending at 3015 m (Hayford Peak). All of these monitoring stations are located on land managed by the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service and several of the stations are co-located with Natural Resource Conservation Service (NRCS) Soil Climate Analysis Network (SCAN) sites. The Snake Range transect has seven monitoring stations beginning at 1790 m on the west side of the range, 3355 m at the western subalpine site and ending at 1560 m on the eastern side of the range. An 8th monitoring station at 1564 m (Salt Desert, west) will be incorporated into the Snake Range transect as funding permits; this site has had an operational eddy covariance system since 2007. The Snake Range transect encompasses several collaborating land holder agencies including: the Long Now Foundation, Bureau of Land Management, Great Basin National Park and the Nevada Land Conservancy.Monitoring stations are located in the elevational \"middle\" of each major plant community/vegetation type along each transect. Table 1 below lists the plant community zone, predominant plant species and altitude for each monitoring station. A <a title=\"Hardware used to monitor the environment and collect data.\" href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Climate%20Monitoring/Equipment.aspx\">configuration of sensors</a> has been installed at each monitoring station including soil and plant sensors, a webcam and standard meteorological sensors.\r\n\r\nTable 1. Site descriptions of locations along the two transects comprising the NevCAN. For data from these locations, visit the <a title=\"Search and download collected sensor data.\" href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Data%20Search/Silverlight%20Data%20Client.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Sensor Data</a> page.\r\n<table id=\"SiteTable\"><colgroup span=\"1\"></colgroup> <colgroup span=\"1\"></colgroup> <colgroup span=\"1\"></colgroup> <colgroup span=\"1\"></colgroup>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Transect</th>\r\n<th>Zone</th>\r\n<th>Dominant Plant Species</th>\r\n<th>Altitude (m)</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Snake</td>\r\n<td>Salt Desert (west)</td>\r\n<td>Sarcobatus vermiculatus, Artemisia tridentata tridentata</td>\r\n<td>1564</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Snake</td>\r\n<td>Sagebrush (west)</td>\r\n<td>Artemisia tridentata tridentata, Sarcobatus vermiculatus</td>\r\n<td>1790</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Snake</td>\r\n<td>Pinyon-Juniper (west)</td>\r\n<td>Pinus monophylla, Juniperus osteosperma</td>\r\n<td>2200</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Snake</td>\r\n<td>Montane (west)</td>\r\n<td>Abies concolor, Pinus flexilis</td>\r\n<td>2810</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Snake</td>\r\n<td>Subalpine (west)</td>\r\n<td>Pinus longaeva, Pinus flexilis</td>\r\n<td>3355</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Snake</td>\r\n<td>Subalpine (east)</td>\r\n<td>Picea engelmannii</td>\r\n<td>3070</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Snake</td>\r\n<td>Sagebrush (east)</td>\r\n<td>Artemisia tridentata tridentata</td>\r\n<td>1835</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Snake</td>\r\n<td>Salt Desert (east)</td>\r\n<td>Sarcobatus vermiculatus, Atriplex confertifolia</td>\r\n<td>1560</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Sheep</td>\r\n<td>Desert Shrub</td>\r\n<td>Larrea tridentata, Ambrosia dumosa</td>\r\n<td>900</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Sheep</td>\r\n<td>Blackbrush</td>\r\n<td>Yucca brevifolia, Atriplex canescens</td>\r\n<td>1670</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Sheep</td>\r\n<td>Pinyon-Juniper</td>\r\n<td>Pinus monophylla, Purshia stansburiana</td>\r\n<td>2065</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Sheep</td>\r\n<td>Montane</td>\r\n<td>Pinus ponderosa, Juniperus osteosperma</td>\r\n<td>2320</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Sheep</td>\r\n<td>Subalpine</td>\r\n<td>Pinus longaeva, Ribes cereum</td>\r\n<td>3015</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</section><section id=\"Right\"></section>&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Research Sites', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '9-revision-v1', '', '', '2012-12-11 17:24:17', '2012-12-11 17:24:17', '', '9', 'http://nccp.monterey-j.com/9-revision-6/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('290', '5', '2012-12-11 17:20:02', '2012-12-11 17:20:02', 'The Nevada Climate Change Project is dedicated to collaboration and public education. Questions regarding collaborative efforts, members, developed technologies, climate research, and general comments or inquiries are always welcome. Please direct your inquiries or comments to:\r\n<ul id=\"EmailList\">\r\n	<li><a href=\"mailto:Gayle.Dana@dri.edu\">Gayle Dana</a> (Project Principal Investigator)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"mailto:Nick.Lancaster@dri.edu\">Nick Lancaster</a> (Project Co-Principal Investigator)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"mailto:Lynn.Fenstermaker@dri.edu\">Lynn Fenstermaker</a> (Science/Research, Transects)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"mailto:Jay.Arnone@dri.edu\">Jay Arnone</a> (Science/Research, Transects)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"mailto:dascalus@cse.unr.edu\">Sergiu Dascalu</a> (Cyberinfrastructure)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"mailto:mcmahon@cse.unr.edu\">Michael J. McMahon Jr.</a> (Cyberinfrastructure, Website, Database, General Information)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAdditional contact information by individual can be found on the <a title=\"Collaborators and other persons involved with the Nevada Climate Change Project.\" href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/People/Default.aspx\">People page</a>.', 'Contact', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '21-revision-4', '', '', '2012-12-11 17:20:02', '2012-12-11 17:20:02', '', '21', 'http://nccp.monterey-j.com/21-revision-4/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('291', '5', '2013-04-30 05:19:11', '2013-04-30 05:19:11', 'The Nevada Climate Change Project is dedicated to collaboration and public education. Questions regarding collaborative efforts, members, developed technologies, climate research, and general comments or inquiries are always welcome. Please direct your inquiries or comments to:\r\n<ul id=\"EmailList\">\r\n	<li><a href=\"mailto:Gayle.Dana@dri.edu\">Gayle Dana</a> (Project Principal Investigator)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"mailto:Nick.Lancaster@dri.edu\">Nick Lancaster</a> (Project Co-Principal Investigator)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"mailto:Lynn.Fenstermaker@dri.edu\">Lynn Fenstermaker</a> (Science/Research, Transects)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"mailto:Jay.Arnone@dri.edu\">Jay Arnone</a> (Science/Research, Transects)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"mailto:dascalus@cse.unr.edu\">Sergiu Dascalu</a> (Cyberinfrastructure)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"mailto:mcmahon@cse.unr.edu\">Michael J. McMahon Jr.</a> (Cyberinfrastructure, Website, Database, General Information)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAdditional contact information by individual can be found on the <a title=\"Collaborators and other persons involved with the Nevada Climate Change Project.\" href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/People/Default.aspx\">People page (main site)</a>.', 'Contact', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '21-revision-5', '', '', '2013-04-30 05:19:11', '2013-04-30 05:19:11', '', '21', 'http://nccp.monterey-j.com/21-revision-5/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('362', '5', '2013-04-30 05:29:09', '2013-04-30 05:29:09', '<h2>Project Participants</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<figure><a title=\"The Nevada System of Higher Education.\" href=\"http://www.nevada.edu\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"height: 50px; width: 50px;\" title=\"The Nevada System of Higher Education.\" alt=\"NSHE\" src=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/images/Institution%20logos/NSHE.svg\" /></a>\r\n<figcaption><a title=\"The Nevada System of Higher Education.\" href=\"http://www.nevada.edu\" target=\"_blank\">Nevada System of Higher Education</a></figcaption></figure><figure><a title=\"Great Basin College.\" href=\"http://www.gbcnv.edu/\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"height: 50px; width: 50px;\" title=\"Great Basin College.\" alt=\"GBC\" src=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/images/Institution%20logos/GBC.svg\" /></a>\r\n<figcaption><a title=\"Great Basin College.\" href=\"http://www.gbcnv.edu/\" target=\"_blank\">Great Basin College</a></figcaption></figure><figure><a title=\"The Desert Research Institute.\" href=\"http://www.dri.edu\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"height: 50px; widt