ain specific scientific research techniques or topics.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Education/Articles/Carbon%20Footprint.docx\">Carbon Footprint</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Education/Articles/Electric%20Conductivity%20of%20Soil.doc\">Electric Conductivity of Soil</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Education/Articles/Introduction%20to%20Transect%20Data.doc\">Introduction to Transect Data</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Education/Articles/Volumetric%20Water%20Content.doc\">Volumetric Water Content</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Education/Articles/Weather%20v%20Climate.docx\">Weather v. Climate</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://sensor.nevada.edu/NCCP/Education/Articles/Wind%20Speed.doc\">Wind Speed</a>\r\n\r\nStudents and instructors are encouraged to enhance their understanding of climate research by undertaking some research of their own, using the data collected by the project in the classroom or for projects. The live web cameras and site conditions are also available throughout the day.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Education', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-04-30 05:33:20', '2013-04-30 05:33:20', '', '13', 'http://nccp.monterey-j.com/13-revision-26/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('297', '5', '2013-04-30 05:38:16', '2013-04-30 05:38:16', 'A number of educational materials and informative articles are made available that explain various aspects of the research that is conducted as a part of the project.\r\n\r\nHands-on experiments are designed for provide instructors with interactive exercises that enhance student understanding of the environment and research. Below are links for each age group. (Click on the age group to expand the section.)\r\n<h3 class=\"collapse\">Elementary School</h3>\r\n<div class=\"collapse-content\">\r\n<a href=\"http://nccp.monterey-j.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Air-Pollution-Experiment.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Air Pollution Experiment</a>\r\n